				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I like to use page 1 for variables, because it's the natural continuation of page 0, where most of my variables usually are. I don't use pages 3 and up for small variables, just for the big tables/buffers/lists.
<br />
<br />Another thing I often have in page 1 is the copy of the attribute tables (128 bytes), something some times of projects benefit from (scrollers where you need to read-modify-write attribute bytes, for example).</div>

